e="preserve">The Fifth Netanyahu Government is the 35th government of Israel and was installed on May 17, 2020.
The Prime Minister is Likud politician Benjamin Netanyahu. In a year and a half Blue and White leader Benny Gantz will become prime minister.
Together it has 74 seats in the 23rd Knesset.
The Fifth Netanyahu Government presents itself as a unity government, established due to health and socio-economic problems caused by the coronavirus pandemic.
